foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: The PS saw an increase in the number of backlogged requests for Fiscal Year 2011 (FY10 - 29 vs. FY11 - 75). The increase in the number of backlogged requests is attributable to several items: 1) the number of requests received compared to last fiscal year increased by 319 (FY10 - 1,318 vs. FY11 - 1,637); however, the number of requests processed for the year increased by 244 when compared to last fiscal year (FY10 - 1,320 vs. FY11 - 1,564); 2) the PS Records Office was not at full complement in Fiscal Year 2011 due to a freeze on hiring, and it lost its administrative support due to the PS organizational redesign.
